OL,3,CIs the BBC Red Button Text service
OL,4,Cserving a useful purpose?
OL,6,GIs it time for the BBC's Red Button
OL,7,GText service to be put out of its
OL,8,Gmisery?
OL,10,FThe service ` with faint echoes of the
OL,11,Fbeloved Ceefax ` was due to close 4
OL,12,Fyears ago.
OL,14,FIt was unexpectedly spared execution
OL,15,Fbecause of the pandemic.
OL,17,FUnderstandably the need to ensure
OL,18,Faccurate information was made as
OL,19,Fwidely available as possible in a dire
OL,20,Femergency took precedence.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G1/7
