OL,3,CIs the BBC Red Button Text service
OL,4,Cserving a useful purpose?
OL,6,FIt is right that the BBC was very
OL,7,Fcautious about shutting down SD
OL,8,Fsatellite services and appears to be
OL,9,Fadopting a very careful approach to
OL,10,Fending AM radio transmission.
OL,12,FI also cannot envisage BBC Freeview
OL,13,Ftransmission ending in the foreseeable
OL,14,Ffuture (i.e., the next 10 to 15 years)
OL,15,Feven if Freely proves a big success
OL,16,Fand some may push for an end to DTT.
OL,18,FBut about the only thing that can be
OL,19,Fsaid in defence of the legacy red
OL,20,Fbutton service is that it must be
OL,21,Fcosting practically nothing.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/7
