OL,3,CIs the BBC Red Button Text service
OL,4,Cserving a useful purpose?
OL,6,FIf the BBC, legitimately, believes
OL,7,Fthis service still has some value to
OL,8,Fpart of the audience then it needs to
OL,9,Factually take the service seriously
OL,10,Fagain.
OL,12,FIf nothing else, could someone be made
OL,13,Foperationally and editorially
OL,14,Fresponsible for what actually appears
OL,15,Fon it? There's no need to create a job
OL,16,Fand spend money. Make it the
OL,17,Fresponsibility of someone on a
OL,18,Fparticular shift.
OL,20,FChoose the stories that work for the
OL,21,Fservice, place them in an appropriate
OL,22,Forder and ensure they make sense!
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/7
